{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.044Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-head attention runs "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "several attention operations in parallel",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", each with its own projections, then concatenates the results. LLMs behind agents use this to capture diverse relationships—syntax, entity links, format patterns—simultaneously rather than forcing one attention pattern to do everything."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "With "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "h"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " heads and model dimension "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "d_{\\text{model}}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", each head typically uses dimension "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "d_k = d_v = d_{\\text{model}} / h"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Head "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " computes "
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\text{head}_i = \\text{Attention}(QW_Q^{(i)}, KW_K^{(i)}, VW_V^{(i)})"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Outputs are concatenated and projected: "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\text{MHA}(Q,K,V) = \\text{Concat}(\\text{head}_1,\\ldots,\\text{head}_h)W_O"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A single attention distribution might focus on immediate neighbors. Multiple heads can specialize: one head may track delimiter tokens for JSON tool calls; another may link pronouns to entities; another may align numbered steps in a plan. Specialization emerges from training rather than manual design."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# h heads, d_model divisible by h\n# Q,K,V: (batch, seq, d_model)\n# Per head: project to (batch, seq, d_head), attend, merge\nd_head = d_model // num_heads\nQ_h = Q.view(batch, seq, num_heads, d_head).transpose(1, 2)\n# ... attention per head ...\nout = out.transpose(1, 2).contiguous().view(batch, seq, d_model)\nout = out @ W_O"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Richer representations without widening a single attention softmax"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Parallel heads map well to GPU tensor cores"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Empirically strong inductive bias for language and structured output"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "More parameters in "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "inlineMath",
                    "attrs": {
                      "latex": "W_Q, W_K, W_V, W_O"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " per layer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Total compute still "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "inlineMath",
                    "attrs": {
                      "latex": "O(n^2 \\cdot h)"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — heads multiply work within each layer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Individual head interpretability is approximate; heads may not stay cleanly \"specialized\""
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance and scalability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Inference engines fuse multi-head projections into fewer matrix multiplies. For agents, latency scales with context length and layer count; multi-head design is why wider models (more heads / larger "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "d_{\\text{model}}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") cost more per token even at the same context length."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mental model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Imagine several reviewers reading the same document, each instructed to notice different cues—one watches dates, one tracks names, one checks formatting—then a lead editor merges their notes into one summary per sentence."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Multiple parallel attention heads → concat → output projection"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Each head uses lower dimension "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "inlineMath",
                    "attrs": {
                      "latex": "d_{\\text{model}}/h"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Enables diverse relational patterns needed for language and tool-use formatting"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dominant cost remains sequence-length quadratic per layer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
